            <fr:title text="Sheaf">Sheaf</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Given a category <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> equipped with a <fr:link href="algm-0019.xml" title="Coverage" addr="algm-0019" type="local">coverage</fr:link>, we define a presheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P : \mathcal {C}^\textrm {op} \to  \mathsf {Set}]]></fr:tex> to be a <fr:strong>sheaf</fr:strong> if it satisfies the <fr:strong>sheaf condition</fr:strong>: for every cover of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, the map from sections of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to <fr:link href="algm-001D.xml" title="Descent data of presheaves" addr="algm-001D" type="local">descent data</fr:link> of the cover is a bijection. It is a <fr:strong>separated presheaf</fr:strong> if the map is an injection.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
